summary: 10/08/1993: Anti-terrorist police arrested five men hours after two related Irish Republican Army bombs rocked parts of north London. The two small devices wrecked buildings but caused no injuries. The second of these incidents took place on West End Lane.
motive: The attack was perpetrated in an effort to derail peace talks.
addnotes: This was one of two related attacks (cf. 199310080001).
scite1: "Two Blasts Reported in North London,” The Associated Press Worldstream, October 9, 1993.
scite2: "Bomb Blasts in North London,” The Guardian (London), October 9, 1993.
scite3: "2 IRA Bombs Shake London; 5 are Arrested,” Chicago Tribune, October 10, 1993.
